snippet.textDisplay:
Alright. Being a Pakistani one should carefully listen to all Coke Studio India songs, and than comment (Since it is hard to swallow anything critical from another nation:-). These were the best ones that I like:

 -- Peekaboo-Karsh Kale (everything good except the damn rappers and English lyrics are annoying)
 -- Dilruba-Kailash (flawless)
 -- Dinae Dinae- Papon (flawless)
 -- Tauba- Papon (flawless)
 -- Yaar Basainda-Saint Thyagaraaja (everything good, though male singing could be improved)
 -- Hoo-Harshdeep Kaur (everything good except the vocals are a bit too echoed)
 -- Mauj Naina (flawless)
 -- Husna-Hitesh Sonik (flawless)
 -- Khwajababa-Shaantanu Moitra (flawless)
 -- Khumaar-Papon (flawless)
 -- Tokari-Papon (flawless)

Based on the Coke Studio India songs alone, I think Papon is the most gifted musician. Coke Studio India should let him take control :-)
Do share your favourites from Coke Studio Pakistan. 
Keep up the good work.
Love from a Lahori :-)

National integraton on Music :-)
